<a id="introduction"></a>
<h4>Introduction</h4>

Ordering Management System, OMS in the future, was developed to handle ordering of car models by different categories of clients including retailers and distributors. While ordering is done exclusively by clients, that is users that have 'client' role assigned to them, system itself is managed by 2 privileged roles: "staff" and "administrator".
This section of the help file describes functionality available to "clients"

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<a id="ordering"></a>
<h4>Ordering</h4>

Ordering is done by registered clients only. 
<p>
To order products go to product list and add products to shopping cart using <Add> button in product row.
</p>
<p>
Shopping cart symbol will pop up in upper right corner of the page. It will show the number of added products. Once selection is complete and all products are added to shopping cart, you can finalize the order by clicking on shopping cart symbol which will open shopping cart modal, where you can either submit order or clear shopping cart and start from the beginning. Number of items for each product can also be adjusted at this stage before submitting the order. 
</p>

<p>
Once order is submitted several things will happen: 

<ul>
<li> - New order is created and added to client list of orders </li>
<li> - Order confirmation email is sent </li>
<li> - PO and Invoice for the new order are generated and order is assigned 'Pending' status </li>
</ul>


