<a id="navigation"></a>
<h4>Navigation & Search</h4>

Navigating through pages in OMS is pretty straightforward. All pages have pagination footer at the bottom where you can either go back and forth by one page, or select page number and go directly to it. As a productivity shortcut, you can also use <back> and <forward> keys on your keyboard to flip through pages.
<p>

Search box is located in page header an is context-sensitive. That is, in Products page you can use it to search for products, in Orders page for order and so forth. Currently products can be searched using complete or partial reference codes, or name. Orders can be searched by number, client name, product reference code. To see available search options, just move your mouse pointer over <Find ..> search box and wait a second. Label will pop up and list available searches. 
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<a id="menu_descriptions"></a>
<h4>Menu Descriptions</h4>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<!-- Products index page -->
<a id="products"></a>
<dt class="col-sm-1">Products</dt>

<dd class="col-sm-11">This page shows list of all active products currently present in database. Reference Code column is linked to product profile which will show product picture and different product attributes, like color, type, brand, scale and others. To add product to shopping cart, just press <Add> button in the last column.
</dd>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<!-- Orders index page -->
<a id="orders"></a>
<dt class="col-sm-1">Orders</dt>

<dd class="col-sm-11">This page shows list of your orders, most recent first. #Products column shows number of different products bought, while #Pcs column will show total number of pieces ordered. Table header shows number of Pending, Active, Shipped and Canceled orders. Each category links to the page showing corresponding orders
<p>
<Find Order> control at the top of the page allows you to filter orders by order number, reference code, etc. PO column links to PO in PDF format. Grand total at the bottom shows total value of all orders in your client currency using current USD/EUR FX conversion rate (if applicable) shown in the footer.
</p>
</dd>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<!-- Documents index page -->
<a id="documents"></a>
<dt class="col-sm-1">Documents</dt>
<dd class="col-sm-11">This section gives you access to reports and other documents. Currently there are 2 report types:
<ul>
  <li> - Client reports: index page with all your client reports. It has <Create Client Report> button at the bottom where you can use different options, like "Time Frame", "Order Status" and "Detail Level" to generate your custom reports. Once report is generated, you can show it by clicking on the Report Id in the first column, download it using <i class='glyphicon glyphicon-download'></i> icon, or create spreadsheet export file by clicking on <i class='glyphicon glyphicon-export'></i> icon.</li>
  <li> - Product reports: this page lists all the product reports that you created. To generate new report, click <Create Product Report> button and then select different options for the new report. Just like in case of Client report you can download newly generated product report in PDF and CSV format.
  </li>
</ul>

</dd>

